The page you’re looking for can’t be found.
But we did find this little treasure
Motorola launched the Personal Phone in 1992. Until then the two providers, Vodafone and Cellnet, had the business market covered, but mobile phones were, as yet, still too expensive for consumers.
The phone only had three function keys: 'Power,' 'Send,' and 'Call End.'
